   282→            <div class="theorem-box">
   283→                <h3>Main Theorem</h3>
   284→                <div class="theorem-statement">
   285→theorem rotated_roots_yield_chebyshev (N : ℕ) (φ : ℝ) (hN : 0 < N) :<br>
   286→&nbsp;&nbsp;∃ (c : ℝ), scaledPolynomial N φ = Polynomial.Chebyshev.T ℝ N + C c
   287→                </div>
   288→                <p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
   289→                    <a href="./docs/ChebyshevCircles/MainTheorem.html#rotated_roots_yield_chebyshev" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500;">View theorem statement in API docs →</a>
   290→                </p>
   291→                <div class="construction">
   292→                    <strong>Construction:</strong>
   293→                    <ul>
   294→                        <li>Projected roots: <code>cos(φ + 2πk/N)</code> for k = 0, ..., N-1 <a href="./blueprint/sect0002.html" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem;">(blueprint §2)</a></li>
   295→                        <li>Unscaled polynomial: <code>P(x) = ∏(x - cos(φ + 2πk/N))</code> <a href="./blueprint/sect0003.html" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem;">(blueprint §3)</a></li>
   296→                        <li>Scaled polynomial: <code>S(x) = 2<sup>N-1</sup> · P(x)</code> <a href="./blueprint/sect0003.html" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem;">(blueprint §3)</a></li>
   297→                        <li>Result: <code>S(x) = T<sub>N</sub>(x) + c(φ)</code> <a href="./blueprint/sect0001.html" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem;">(blueprint §1)</a></li>
   298→                    </ul>
